{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0808ca6c-4fd7-4e3f-8089-8a851058d96a","content":"Here's what you need to change in your `.csproj`:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` NuGet meta-package (v3.x) — it bundles the test framework, adapter, and analyzers\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\nYour test code (`using` statements, attributes, assertions) is already compatible — MSTest v3 uses the same `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace.\n\nHere's the updated `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net462</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.13.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n- ❌ Remove `<Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />`\n- ✅ Add `MSTest` 3.8.3 (replaces the old assembly ref)\n- ✅ Bump `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to 17.13.0\n\nWant me to apply these changes and verify the project builds?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1a0ff00e-23e5-46e0-ae7f-7f1fc8d06e73","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has:\n\n1. An SDK-style project targeting `net462`\n2. An assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` (the old MSTest v1 approach)\n3. `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` 17.5.0\n4. Test code using `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace\n\nTo upgrade to MSTest v3, they need to:\n\n1. **Remove** the assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n\n\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` NuGet meta-package (v3.x) which bundles the test framework, adapter, and analyzers together\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` if needed, though the current version should work fine\n4. **Consider updating the TFM** — while `net462` is still supported by MSTest v3, upgrading to a newer framework version would be beneficial\n5. The `using Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;` namespace will continue to work as-is\n\n, and the `[Timeout]` attribute with millisecond values remains compatible\n\nThe main action items are removing the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` and adding the `MSTest` NuGet package instead.","outputTokens":955,"requestId":"23CE:A9EA2:4224B5:46F958:6A031077"},"id":"0126328d-67a9-4e19-a21e-0b06e057f506","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:35:40.921Z","parentId":"e6cce9ad-2582-41a0-9ab0-d0e2fa38e015"}
